Yes or No?<br />
<br />
While SOE is &quot;Fixing&quot; manaburn take a look at Frenzied devistation up the crit rate more<br />
<br />
Any shot of them maybe using the new pull down maps to give us the ability to have a AA port that lets us drop a map marker for our port location in any zone we are in tht has map access.<br />
<br />
Spell effects personaly i feel like the effects in game for our class have no imagination what so ever sometimes and while its a purely cosmetic desire and theres a ton of actual ballance concerns for us that need to be addressed first I would like to eventually see some better spell effects.<br />
<br />
Personaly i think at times we have the worst spell effects in game if your doing a godly damage spell it should look amazing as well some ideas<br />
<br />
Claw of Vox invokes the essence of the ice dragon have a effect that looks like a giant dragon claw hiting the mob not a ice block falling from the sky.<br />
<br />
ON crit blasts on large nukes have a additional effect maybe viewable from far away ... for fire nukes a giant mushroom cloud effect .  for lightning a giant swirling electrical tempest that makes a pillar of lightning that goes from the zone ceilings to the mob and can be seen from the distance. For ice have clouds from from overhead and swirl together and drop the commet blasts.<br />
<br />
On the faster nukes have a beam type effect flow from the wizard to the mobs.<br />
<br />
On Reinvisionment and our grouping abilities <br />
<br />
Personaly i feel that most players when making a group base the group on what other classes can bring to them. When a tank and cleric meet the tank brings damage tanking and ability to hold aggro the cleric brings heals and buffs and exp recovery in case of death. The then look for Slowers and manabuffers for the cleric  or other healer.<br />
<br />
The problem we face is that our abilites do not directly enhance the groups abilites at all and we have 2 classes of wizards the ones that are at end game level of play and nuke in the 10 to 12 k range and get groups based on the damage we are capable of with those end game spells and the rest that are not end game players and nuke in the 6 to 8k range and they become frustrated. <br />
<br />
IF wizards had any of the following abilites <br />
Group harvest (as a persentage of current mana pool)<br />
Group Familiar (stackable mana regen for group and increase mana pool)<br />
Group Nuke Proc ability (The wizards offensive casts are randomly infused into the weapons of group members) <br />
<br />
You would see wizards greatly wanted in groups.<br />
<br />
With the event of giving shamans and druids increased abilites via aa resurection for no exp would it be out of balance to give wizards the reverse of a necro corpse summon ability. Transloc to body ? target a player character on a corpse run and tl them to there most current body ?</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
